"title": "1025: God, anger of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1025: god, anger of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The punitive and vindicatory reaction, legitimate and controlled, yet awesomely emphatic, of God the righteous judge to unrighteousness in his human creatures. Up to the present, the expression of God's anger and wrath has had the purpose of drawing sinners to repentance and conversion, but this will not be the case at the final judgment.</p>\n<h2>The nature of God's anger</h2>\n<h3>It is fearsome</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:6\">NAM 1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:26\">JOS 7:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:18\">EZK 38:18</a></p>\n<h3>It is reluctant and short-lived</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:6\">EXO 34:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:7-Isa54:8\">ISA 54:7–54:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:16-Neh9:18\">NEH 9:16–9:18</a></p>\n<h3>It is consistant with his righteous and merciful character</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:11\">PSA 7:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:2\">HAB 3:2</a></p>\n<h3>It fulfils God's purposes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:20\">JER 23:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:24\">JER 30:24</a></p>\n<h2>The causes of God's anger</h2>\n<h3>Idolatry and unbelief</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num25:3\">NUM 25:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:8-Exod32:10\">EXO 32:8–32:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:19\">DEU 8:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:10-Judg2:14\">JDG 2:10–2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:9\">1KI 14:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:32-1Kgs16:33\">1KI 16:32–16:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:53\">1KI 22:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:19\">2KI 23:19</a> <em>Josiah removes idolatrous shrines</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:25\">2CH 28:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:25\">2CH 34:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:19\">JER 8:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:29\">JER 32:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:3\">JER 44:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:36\">JHN 3:36</a> <em>the unbelief of rejecting the Son of God</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:18-Rom1:23\">ROM 1:18–1:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:8\">ROM 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Disobedience and disloyalty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:1\">JOS 7:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:7\">DEU 9:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:13\">2KI 22:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:10\">1CH 13:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:29\">PSA 106:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:32\">JER 32:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:13\">ZEC 7:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:6\">EPH 5:6</a></p>\n<h3>Ungodly living</h3>\n<p>God's judgment against the ungodly is a sign of his anger against actions that contradict his righteous character and purposes:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:1-2Tim3:9\">2TI 3:1–3:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:14-Jude1:16\">JUD 1:14–1:16</a></p>\n<h3>Pride, arrogance and hypocrisy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:27-Matt23:28\">MAT 23:27–23:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:25\">2CH 32:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:34\">PRO 3:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:13\">PRO 8:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:11\">ISA 13:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:14\">HOS 12:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:1\">MAL 4:1</a></p>\n<h3>Complaints against, and opposition to, God's purposes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:1\">NUM 11:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:27\">NUM 14:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:5\">NUM 21:5</a></p>\n<h3>Injustice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:9-Zech7:12\">ZEC 7:9–7:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr19:7\">2CH 19:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:13\">JER 22:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek9:9\">EZK 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:5\">MAL 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:23\">MAT 23:23</a></p>\n<h3>The rejection of God's servants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:29-Heb10:31\">HEB 10:29–10:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:35-Deut32:36\">DEU 32:35–32:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:14\">PSA 135:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:26\">NEH 9:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:12\">ZEC 7:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:33-Matt21:41\">MAT 21:33–21:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:35-Acts7:37\">ACT 7:35–7:37</a></p>\n<h2>God reveals his anger</h2>\n<h3>In present times</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:18\">ROM 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:10\">JER 10:10</a></p>\n<h3>On a future ``day of wrath'' which is anticipated</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:5\">ROM 2:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:9\">ISA 13:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:13\">ISA 13:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek7:19\">EZK 7:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:15\">ZEP 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:18\">ZEP 1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph2:2\">ZEP 2:2</a></p>\n<h2>The consequences of God's anger</h2>\n<h3>God allows those who reject righteousness to remain in their sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:18-Rom1:32\">ROM 1:18–1:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:16\">1KI 14:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:5\">2CH 12:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:28\">NEH 9:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:7-Isa54:8\">ISA 54:7–54:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:27-Jer7:29\">JER 7:27–7:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:7-Jer12:8\">JER 12:7–12:8</a></p>\n<h3>Punishment will be experienced by rebellious people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:19\">DEU 8:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:18\">ISA 59:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer21:14\">JER 21:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:34-Matt18:35\">MAT 18:34–18:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:28-Matt25:30\">MAT 25:28–25:30</a>EXO <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:12\">12:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:13\">NUM 32:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:25-Josh7:26\">JOS 7:25–7:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:9-Isa13:13\">ISA 13:9–13:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:30\">DAN 5:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:5\">ACT 5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:101\">ACT 5:101</a>KI <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:15\">14:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:13-Jer15:14\">JER 15:13–15:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:7-Jer25:11\">JER 25:7–25:11</a>LAM <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:1-Jer2:9\">2:1–2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:19-Ezek38:21\">EZK 38:19–38:21</a></p>\n<h3>God will be feared as his holiness and greatness are revealed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:18-Isa59:19\">ISA 59:18–59:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:22-Ezek38:23\">EZK 38:22–38:23</a></p>\n<h3>Ultimately God will purify and restore his people for service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:2-Mal3:4\">MAL 3:2–3:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:19-Jer15:21\">JER 15:19–15:21</a></p>",
